GREEN RIVER WIND FARM PHASE 1, LLC RATE SCHEDULE FERC NO. 2
Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service
Green River Wind Farm Phase 1, LLC ("GRWF") provides Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service ("Reactive Supply Service") from a wind generating facility located in Lee County and Whiteside County, Illinois, within the Commonwealth Edison Company ("ComEd") Zone of the control area administered by PJM Interconnection, L.L.C. ("PJM") in order to assist in maintaining transmission voltages within acceptable limits on the PJM transmission system. This Rate Schedule sets forth GRWF's revenue requirement for the provision of Reactive Supply Service, as contemplated by Schedule 2 of the PJM Open Access Transmission Tariff, which provides that PJM will pay generation owners their monthly revenue requirement for Reactive Supply Service. This Rate Schedule shall be effective upon the date authorized by the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission. REVENUE REQUIREMENT: Total Revenue Requirement: GRWF's Total Annual Revenue Requirement shall be calculated as follows: Fixed Annual Revenue Requirement is: $710,000.04 Monthly Revenue Requirement is: $59,166.67 (based on Fixed Annual Revenue Requirement divided by 12)
